1. Core Infrastructure (2-3 weeks)

   ├── Transaction Management
   │   ├── Borsh serialization
   │   ├── Transaction building
   │   └── Fee calculation
   
   ├── Network Layer
   │   ├── RPC client implementation
   │   └── Connection management

2. Security Hardening

   ├── Keypair management
   │   ├── Key generation
   │   ├── Key storage
   │   └── Key retrieval
   
   ├── Transaction signing
   │   ├── Signing interface
   │   └── Signature verification

3. Solana-specific Features (2-3 weeks)

   ├── Program deployment
   │   ├── Program ID generation
   │   ├── Program deployment
   │   └── Program verification
   
   ├── Program invocation
   │   ├── RPC client integration
   │   └── Transaction building

4. Testing and Documentation (1-2 weeks)

   ├── Unit tests
   │   ├── Keypair tests
   │   ├── Transaction tests
   │   └── Network tests
   
   ├── Integration tests
   │   ├── RPC client integration tests
   │   └── Transaction building tests

## Critical Tasks for Each Milestone

### Core Infrastructure
 - Implement Borsh serialization for transactions
 - Build RPC client with retry logic
 - Add transaction versioning support
 - Implement fee calculation

### Security Hardening
 - Implement key generation and storage
 - Implement transaction signing and verification
 - Add key rotation support

### Solana-specific Features
- Implement program deployment and verification
 - Implement program invocation

### Testing and Documentation
 - Implement unit tests
 - Implement integration tests
 - Document the project

